'''Anthony Kumpen''' (born 3 November 1978) is a Belgian professional racing driver. As the overall winner of the [[2014 NASCAR Whelen Euro Series season]], he received his license to compete in the [[2015 NASCAR Sprint Cup Series]]. 

==Career==
In 1988, Kumpen started [[Kart racing]]. He moved on to [[Belcar]], the Belgian Racing Car Championship, in 1998, winning the GT2 championship in his first year, and the GT championship in 1999. He won several more Belgian GT and GTA championships over the next decade. In 2000, he won the overall classification at the [[24 Hours of Zolder]], a feat he would repeat in 2002, 2003, 2004, 2010 and 2012 for a record total of 6 victories.<ref>{{cite web|title=SPORTWEEKEND: Monza en Zolder|url=http://www.autowereld.be/2012/09/10/sportweekend-monza-en-zolder/|website=Autowereld.be|accessdate=21 November 2014|language=Dutch|date=10 September 2012}}</ref>

In 2000, he started competing in the [[FIA GT Championship]] for the [[Paul Belmondo]] Racing team. His first victory in a race in this championship followed in 2002. More victories followed in 2005 (2), 2006, 2008 and 2009 (2).<ref>{{cite web|title=Anthony Kumpen|url=https://www.driverdb.com/drivers/anthony-kumpen/|website=driverdb.com|accessdate=27 November 2014}}</ref>

He also competed in the [[24 Hours of Daytona]] and the [[24 Hours of Le Mans]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Anthony Kumpen|url=http://racing-reference.info/driver/Anthony_Kumpen|website=racingreference.info|accessdate=27 November 2014}}</ref>

In 2014, he competed in the [[NASCAR Whelen Euro Series]] for the [[PK Carsport]] team, driving a Chevrolet [[Super Sport]]. He won one race in the championship, and ended the season in first place, one point ahead of defending champion [[Ander Vilari<U+00F1>o]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Estrada|first1=Chris|title=NASCAR: Belgium<U+2019>s Kumpen takes Whelen Euro Series title at Le Mans|url=http://motorsportstalk.nbcsports.com/2014/10/14/nascar-belgiums-kumpen-takes-whelen-euro-series-title-at-le-mans/|work=NBC|date=14 October 2014}}</ref>

His win gave him a license to compete in the [[2015 NASCAR Sprint Cup Series]], although it is not yet known for which team he will race. His schedule for this season includes twelve races, in which he hopes to score enough points to return afterwards for a full season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Anthony Kumpen volgend seizoen in het Nascar: "Dit is een unieke kans"|url=http://www.demorgen.be/sport/anthony-kumpen-volgend-seizoen-in-het-nascar-dit-is-een-unieke-kans-a2124459/|work=De Morgen|agency=Belga|date=18 November 2014|language=Dutch}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Anthony Kumpen is the son of Paul Kumpen, former race pilot, director of the building company Kumpen, and president of [[VOKA]] Limburg. Paul Kumpen owned 50% of the shares of [[Ridley Bikes]], and Anthony worked as a commercial director for the company, which became the largest bike manufacturer in Belgium.<ref name=Gazet/> Anthony stayed on at the company after his father sold his share in 2013.<ref name=Gazet>{{cite news|title=CEO koopt familie Kumpen uit bij Ridley bikes|url=http://www.gva.be/cnt/eid194596/extern-ceo-koopt-familie-kumpen-uit-bij-ridley-bikes|accessdate=21 November 2014|work=Gazet van Antwerpen|agency=Belga|date=15 November 2013|language=Dutch}}</ref>

Kumpen lives in [[Hasselt]] and is married to Griet Vanhees. They have one child, a son named Henri-Constant.<ref>{{cite news|last1=verhoogen|first1=Inne|title=Griet Vanhees is mama van Henri-Constant|url=http://deredactie.be/cm/vrtnieuws/cultuur%2Ben%2Bmedia/media/1.1595048|work=Deredactie.be|language=Dutch}}</ref> Kumpen has an older daughter Laura from a previous relation, and Griet has an older son Thibeau.<ref>{{cite news|last1=jva|title=Racepiloot Anthony Kumpen gehuwd met babe Griet Vanhees|url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/cnt/DMF20110604_029|work=Het Nieuwsblad|date=4 June 2011|language=Dutch}}</ref>

In 2010, Anthony Kumpen participated in ''Sterren op de Dansvloer'' (the Belgian version of [[Dancing with the Stars]]) on [[vtm]].<ref name=Sterren>{{cite web|title=Anthony Kumpen|url=http://vtm.be/sterren-op-de-dansvloer/anthony-kumpen/personage|publisher=vtm|accessdate=21 November 2014|language=Dutch|date=2010}}</ref> He was voted out of the show in the third episode and finished as 8th out of 10 contestants.<ref>{{cite news|title=Anthony Kumpen mag niet meer dansen|url=http://www.standaard.be/cnt/dmf20100416_143|work=De Standaard|date=16 April 2010|language=Dutch}}</ref>

Kumpen is the uncle of [[Max Verstappen]], who is set to become the youngest [[Formula One]] driver in history, racing for [[Scuderia Toro Rosso]] in the [[2015 Formula One season]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bonardel|first1=C<U+00E9>cile|title=Verstappen's son in F1 in 2015|url=http://www.24h-lemans.com/en/news/24-hours-of-le-mans-previous-class-winner-jos-verstappen-s-son-in-f1-in-2015_2_2_1746_16741.html|website=24h-lemans.com|accessdate=24 November 2014|date=18 August 2014}}</ref>

